      "description": "An inverted optical microscope (Zeiss Observer Z.1) with a 63 × oil-immersion objective, coupled to a camera (MU9PC-MH XIMEA and PCO Edge 5.5) was used to record the 2D displacement of single mitochondria. The camera was typically recording 10-s-long videos with a framerate of 30 frames per second (fps). The recorded movies were saved as AVI files. All measurements were carried out at room temperature without phase contrast nor fluorescent staining of the mt-DNA.",
